Third-Party Notices

This project builds on and references the following third-party software and
resources. Components listed under "Build-time dependencies" are fetched by
`scripts/setup-wsl.sh` into `external/` and are not redistributed in this
repository.

Build-time dependencies
-----------------------

ch32fun
  Repository: https://github.com/cnlohr/ch32fun
  License: MIT License
  Copyright (c) 2023-2024 CNLohr <lohr85@gmail.com>, et al.
  Copyright (c) 2021 Nanjing Qinheng Microelectronics Co., Ltd.
  Copyright (c) 2023-2024 E. Brombaugh

rv003usb
  Repository: https://github.com/cnlohr/rv003usb
  License: MIT License
  Copyright (c) 2023 CNLohr

Referenced tools (not bundled)
------------------------------

UIAP Web Flasher
  URL: https://yuukiumeta-uiap.github.io/rv003usb-webflasher/example.html
  Based on: https://github.com/SadaleNet/rv003usb-webflasher
  License: see upstream repository

Hardware and upstream firmware references
-----------------------------------------

UIAPduino Pro Micro CH32V003 V1.4
  Manufacturer / documentation: https://www.uiap.jp/en/uiapduino/pro-micro/ch32v003/v1dot4
  This repository is an independent sample project and is not an official UIAP
  product. Factory bootloader firmware on the board is derived from rv003usb
  with UIAP-specific modifications. Redistribution of UIAP bootloader binaries
  is not included in this repository.

pid.codes USB identifiers
  VID 0x1209 — test range registered via https://pid.codes/
  PID 0xB003 — rv003usb bootloader (cnlohr / MIT)
  PID 0xB803 — UIAP custom bootloader wait mode (factory default on UIAPduino)
  PID 0xD011 — application PID used by this project's firmware (WebHID I/O)
  PID 0xD010 — legacy LED-only firmware (superseded)

WCH CH32V003
  Microcontroller by Nanjing Qinheng Microelectronics Co., Ltd.
